msgid "**Inline-reply media:** `channels.matrix.mention_only = true` makes the bot ignore naked media uploads (no text body to mention against). When the user inline-replies to such a dropped event with a question (`@bot can you see this?`), ZeroClaw walks the reply's `m.relates_to.m.in_reply_to.event_id`, fetches the parent event, and pulls its media into the current message: the agent's vision pipeline sees the image even though the original upload was filtered out."
