#: src/foundations/fnd-005-contribution-culture.md
msgid "**Ownership is not \"I did my part.\"** It is \"I care whether the whole thing works.\" You can own a crate without being indifferent to whether the system that crate lives in is healthy. You can own a feature without being indifferent to whether users can actually use it. Narrow ownership, \"I did my bit, the rest is someone else's problem\", produces systems that technically have owners for every piece and functionally have no one responsible for anything."
