msgid "**Review is not optional because AI wrote it.** The culture RFC named this clearly, and it bears repeating with specifics: when reviewing AI-generated code, the gate questions does it compile, do the tests pass, are the beginning of the review, not the end. The standard questions are: does this handle operational errors correctly, or does it `.unwrap()` them? Is the new public API documented? Does the test assert the behavior or the implementation? Is this near a trust boundary, and if so, does it validate its inputs? These questions are your responsibility regardless of who wrote the code or what tools were used to produce it."
