#: src/setup/freebsd.md
msgid "**`read` from a `daemon -P` pidfile reports a false negative.** `daemon -P` writes the pid with **no trailing newline**, so `IFS= read -r pid < \"${pidfile}\"` returns a _non-zero_ status (EOF before newline) even though it set `pid` correctly. If you guard it as `read -r pid < \"$pf\" || return 1`, every running instance looks stopped and your idempotent `start` happily launches a duplicate. Don't key the success path on `read`'s exit status: validate the value instead:"
msgstr ""

