#: src/contributing/multi-agent-setup.md
msgid "Add another agent through the gateway dashboard, zerocode, or `zeroclaw config set`. The runtime creates `<install>/agents/<alias>/workspace/` on first agent-loop entry. On every start the agent loop injects the workspace identity files that exist into the system prompt: `AGENTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `IDENTITY.md`, `USER.md`, then `BOOTSTRAP.md` (first run only) and `MEMORY.md` (main session only). `HEARTBEAT.md` is also a workspace personality file but it is read by the heartbeat engine, not injected into the prompt. The dashboard's personality editor exposes `SOUL.md`, `IDENTITY.md`, `USER.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`, and `MEMORY.md` for editing. Create and edit those files to give the agent its persona. (`BOOTSTRAP.md` is a first-run scaffold the agent reads once and removes; the editor does not expose it.)"
msgstr ""

