#: src/architecture/logging.md
msgid "The `tracing` crate is `zeroclaw-log`'s implementation detail: the `record!` / `scope!` / `attribution_span!` macros expand to `zeroclaw_log::__private::tracing` so a call site never names a tracing type. The log-event macros themselves (`tracing::{trace,debug,info,warn,error}`, `log::*`, `std::dbg`, plus bare `anyhow::anyhow!`) are **hard-banned workspace-wide** as `disallowed-macros` in `clippy.toml`. With `-D warnings` in CI, any direct `tracing::info!` etc. **fails the build**, with a clippy message naming `::zeroclaw_log::record!` as the replacement. This is not a convention; it is enforced."
