msgid "When **`recover()` itself fails** (typically `MAC check for the secret storage key failed`), the channel logs the homeserver's default secret-storage key id, whether the key event has passphrase info, the whitespace-stripped input length, and the full error chain: these point at _which_ layer rejected the recovery key without leaking the value. Recovery failures are **non-fatal** (they don't trigger auto-wipe); the bot continues, the new device just won't be cross-signed."
