#: src/reference/config.md
msgid "When `url` is set to a non-empty value, registers a `file_download` tool that GETs a file from the configured endpoint and writes it to the agent's workspace filesystem. The LLM supplies only a document identifier and a workspace-relative destination path; the endpoint URL comes solely from this config and is never model-controlled. Response bytes are streamed to disk and never loaded into model context."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/config.md
msgid "When `url` is set to a non-empty value, registers a `file_upload_bundle` tool that POSTs N files from the agent's local filesystem to the configured endpoint as a single `multipart/form-data` request. The LLM provides only file paths; the host reads the bytes."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/config.md
